column1: #Text=A shaft grounding brush assembly for establishing electrical contact between a brush and a rotating shaft to remove a charge from the shaft , the assembling characterized by : an arm ( 72 , 72\u2032 ) having first and second ends ; pivotal mounting means ( 76 , 76\u2032 , 78 , 78\u2032 ) for pivotally mounting said arm at the first end ; brush means ( 70 , 70\u2032 ) attached to said arm at said second end ; and bias means ( 86 , 86\u2032 ) for applying a bias force on said arm at a location between said first and second ends , thereby providing a bias force for urging said brush into contact with a shaft .

#Text=The shaft grounding brush assembly of claim 1 , characterized by said pivotal mounting means including a bracket ( 80 , 80\u2032 ) having a slot ( 78 , 78\u2032 ) , for receiving an edge portion ( 76 , 76\u2032 ) of said arm , wherein said edge portion is located at the first end of said arm .
#Text=The shaft grounding brush assembly of claim 2 , further characterized by stop means ( 100 , 102 ) for limiting lateral movement of said arm along said slot .
#Text=The shaft grounding brush assembly of claim 2 , further characterized by means ( 104 , 104\u2032 ) for preventing removal of said edge portion from said slot .
#Text=The shaft grounding brush assembly of claim 2 , characterized by said bracket including clamping means ( 82 , 82\u2032 ) for mounting the brush assembly on a stud .

#Text=The shaft grounding brush assembly of claim 1 , characterized by said spring means including a negator spring ( 86 , 86\u2032 ) having a first fixed end ( 86a , 86a\u2032 ) and a second end ( 86b , 86b\u2032 ) having a loop .

#Text=The shaft grounding brush assembly of claim 6 , characterized by said assembly including a mounting bracket ( 80 , 80\u2032 ) and wherein said first end of said negator spring is fixed to said mounting bracket .

#Text=The shaft grounding brush assembly of claim 6 , characterized by said arm including roller means ( 88 , 90 , 108 ) in contact with said loop of the negator spring for supporting said loop , whereby the bias force is imparted to said arm through said roller means .

#Text=The shaft grounding brush assembly of claim 8 , characterized by said arm including a V-shaped edge ( 76 , 76\u2032 ) portion located at the first end of the arm , the assembly further including a mounting bracket ( 80 , 80\u2032 ) having a slot for receiving the V-shaped edge portion of the arm , thereby forming the pivotal mounting means for mounting the arm upon the bracket .
